body: I didn't think this file should be checked in.

> This file is intended to be committed into source repositories
https://docs.npmjs.com/files/package-lock.json

This goes against the guidance from Node.js, and seems to me to mostly defeat the purpose of a lock file. I disagree entirely. If you are saying it is Sawtooth policy to go against this guidance, then I will remove it in order to comply with that policy.
Not checking this in allows us to catch issues that will inevitably crop up during library updates during the CI process.  We should ensure that a nightly build is running for this SDK.
There is a Jenkinsfile. @rbuysse would know whether or not a nightly build has been set up.
